race.comment: TWISTED LOVE (10) raced wide and copped interference mid-race but still put her BM64 rivals to the sword over 1850m at Newcastle last start. Lightly raced four-year-old from the Maher stable who looks ready for another crack at a staying trip. Stick with her. Likely leader DORADUS (8) has straightening in front in 1900m races at Canterbury of late but is failing to quite finish off. Can roll along here and although a question mark at the trip should give backers a sight. MEDIARO (6) was an eye-catcher two back over this distance at Gosford then failed to measure up to Sydney Saturday company last time. Can improve in this more suitable contest. DOLCE DIOR (7) resumed with a tough win over the mile at Canberra 12 days ago. Won by panels at her only try over this distance last prep at Orange. Cannot be underestimated. IMPUNITY (2) has failed to feature in two runs this time in work up to a mile. Needs this sort of trip now so watch for a much better performance.
